sql:
SELECT COUNT(work_order_id) as total_completed_work_orders
FROM work_orders
WHERE status = 'Completed';

external_knowledge:
- 'top 3 salespeople' refers to the salespeople with the highest total sales value within each node;
- 'stars of a sales galaxy' is a metaphor for the top-performing salespeople;
- 'constellations' is a metaphor for the different nodes where services are delivered.

- 'Education' industry refers to customers who are part of the education sector;
- 'Most generous benefactor' refers to the customer with the highest total sales value;
- 'Standing tall above the average contributor' means the customer who has spent more than the average amount.

- The lead time is the number of days it takes to receive the part after an order is placed;
- The unit cost is the cost of one unit of the part;
- The total sales value is the sum of the sales values for all transactions involving the part.

sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(node_id) FROM nodes) AS total_nodes,
  (SELECT AVG(annual_revenue) FROM customers) AS average_annual_revenue;

external_knowledge:
- "Total revenue" is the sum of all sales values for a specific part number;
- "Total part cost" is the sum of all part costs for a specific part number;
- "Total labor cost" is the sum of all labor costs for a specific part number;
- "Total other cost" is the sum of all other costs for a specific part number;
- The results are ordered by total revenue in descending order to highlight the most lucrative parts.

- "the vast forest of sales" refers to the overall sales environment;
- "towering giant" refers to the node with the highest average sales;
- "crowned by the highest average sales" means the node has the highest average sales value.

- "significant sales transaction" refers to a transaction with a total sales value greater than 5000;
- "cost of the parts used" refers to the total unit cost of the parts associated with the work order;
- "hierarchy, at level 2" refers to customers who are part of a larger customer organization with more than 1000 employees and are one level below the top-level organization in the hierarchy.

- "Golden request type" refers to the request type with the highest average profit margin;
- "Shines the brightest" is a metaphor for achieving the highest value;
- "Average profit margin" is calculated as (total profit / total sales) * 100;
- "Request type" includes categories like "Only UM" and "Professional Sales".
